== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===

When enabling support to the filesystem in the kernel, it is wise to enable at least the first four options (<var>CONFIG_F2FS_FS</var>, <var>F2FS_FS_XATTR</var>, <var>CONFIG_F2FS_FS_POSIX_ACL</var>, and <var>CONFIG_F2FS_FS_SECURITY</var>).

The final fifth option in the set is filesystem consistency checking. This checking will occur during runtime, therefore decreasing filesystem performance. Be aware of this when enabling this option.

The sixth, and final option, is encryption. If encryption is in the use case, then this option should be enabled as well.

{{KernelBox|title=Enabling basic f2fs filesystem options|1=
File systems  --->
   <*> F2FS filesystem support
   [*]   F2FS extended attributes
   [*]     F2FS Access Control Lists
   [*]     F2FS Security Labels
   [ ]   F2FS consistency checking feature
   [ ]   F2FS Encryption
}}

=== Emerge ===

Install the user space tools for the f2fs filesystem:

{{Emerge|sys-fs/f2fs-tools}}

== Usage ==

=== Creation ===

After emerging the userspace tools, create a filesystem by running the {{c|mkfs.f2fs}} command followed by the appropriate device and partition number:

{{RootCmd|mkfs.f2fs /dev/sdd1}}

=== Filesystem check ===

{{RootCmd|fsck.f2fs /dev/sdd1}}

=== Defragmentation ===

{{RootCmd|defrag.f2fs}}

